    "lemma": "на всякий случай",
    "romaji": "na fsyákiy slúchay",
    "translation": "just in case",
    "naturalMeaning": "The phrase that does the heaviest lifting in this whole pack — how most modern Russians explain why they still follow a superstition they claim not to believe in.",
    "cefr": "A2",
    "register": "neutral",
    "tags": ["core"]
  },
